'''Brooke Castile''' (born on May 31, 1986 in [[Detroit]], [[Michigan]]) is an [[United States|American]] [[pair skating|pair skater]]. She is best known for her partnership with [[Benjamin Okolski]].<ref name =st051212>{{cite news | url = http://www.skatetoday.com/2005/12/12/castile-and-okolski-show-promise/ | title = Castile and Okolski Show Promise | last = Mittan | first = Barry | date = December 12, 2005 | publisher = SkateToday | accessdate = August 12, 2011}}</ref> They are the [[United States Figure Skating Championships|2007 U.S. National Champions]]. They announced their retirement from competitive skating in May 2010.<ref name=retirement>{{cite news | url = http://www.usfigureskating.org/Story.asp?id=44619&type=media | title = Castile and Okolski Announce Retirement from Competitive Figure Skating | last = | first = |date = May 13, 2010 | work = [[U.S. Figure Skating]] | accessdate = May 5, 2011 }}</ref>
==Skating with the Stars== In November 2010 Castile was cast on ABC's [[Skating with the Stars]]. Her partner was [[Jonny Moseley]].<ref>http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2010/11/11/pro-skater-pairings-host-and-color-commentator-for-abcs-skating-with-the-stars-announced-11114/20101111abc03</ref>
